# Per-package environment overrides for cross-compilation
#
# Format: category/package environment-file.conf
#
# Environment files are stored in the portage env/ directory

# Force static, non-PIE linking for ALL packages.
# static.conf adds -static to LDFLAGS, disables PIE (which conflicts with
# static linking on i486/musl), passes --disable-shared to autotools configure,
# and triggers the libtool patch in bashrc (which makes -static actually stick).
#
# This catch-all covers every world package AND every pulled-in dependency.
# Packages that do not compile anything (virtuals, man-pages, app-alternatives)
# ignore these variables harmlessly.
*/*  static.conf
